Thank you for making this module available.

### Issue
When using `v1.3.3` and loading it as a module using the Dojo loader, instead of the callback being the  function `function (blob, name, no_auto_bom)` it is returned as a `number` `3`.

### Details

I have found an issue when upgrading from version `1.3.2` to version `1.3.3`.

In version `1.3.2`, the module code looks as such:

```js
if (typeof module !== "undefined" && module.exports) {
  module.exports.saveAs = saveAs;
} else if ((typeof define !== "undefined" && define !== null) && (define.amd !== null)) {
  define([], function() {
    return saveAs;
  });
}
```

In version `1.3.3`, the module code changed:

```js
if (typeof module !== "undefined" && module.exports) {
  module.exports.saveAs = saveAs;
} else if ((typeof define !== "undefined" && define !== null) && (define.amd !== null)) {
  define("FileSaver.js", function() {
    return saveAs;
  });
}
```

Related doc: Dojo Toolkit Documentation - [Defining modules](https://dojotoolkit.org/documentation/tutorials/1.8/modules/)

### Live sample

 https://jsbin.com/toxajaw/edit?html,console,output

### Related issue

I have not tried other module loaders, but thought this might be related to issue [requirejs module naming](https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/issues/271) #271.

