Here's what IR.md has to say about model domain names:

_Models MUST specify a domain and use reverse domain names based on the responsible organization's identity,[...]_

And here is what onnx.proto has to say, in a comment:

  // Domain name of the model.
  // We use reverse domain names as name space indicators. For example:
  // `com.facebook.fair` or `com.microsoft.cognitiveservices`
  //
  // Together with `model_version` and GraphProto.name, this forms the unique identity of
  // the graph.

The commentary is silent on whether the property must be present or not, while the .proto file will specifically call out properties that must be present in other cases. While the IR.md establishes itself as normative ahead of comments in the .proto file when it comes to semantics, the inconsistency needs to be acknowledged and resolve.
